snippet.textDisplay:
This song is a beauty..only ARR can do it..juxtaposition of a himalayan buddhist's peaceful mind against a sharp contrast..perfectly portrayed through music..
video made well as well..the lamini Ani Choying rested well on a pedestal throughout..with meditative posture and divine serenity..always renouncing the worldy thimgs happening around her..all she did was recite the divine mantra..Kudos to the well thought concept..and much love to all involved. ❤

snippet.textDisplay: With all due respect, the problem is, this song is like a collage of some nice tunes. But those tunes are so different from each other that the end result does not appear that soothing to the ear. It's like eating Biryani with Chilli Chicken- two great dishes but never compatible.
